OL,3,CTeachers thought they were 'going to
OL,4,Cdie' during Ammanford school stabbing
OL,6,FAssistant headteacher Fiona Elias
OL,7,Frecalled how she had spoken to the
OL,8,Fpupil on the morning of the attack
OL,9,Fafter finding her in a school hall she
OL,10,Fwas not permitted to be in.
OL,12,FMs Elias described the pupil as having
OL,13,F"a sinister look in her eye" and
OL,14,F"playing with an object in her pocket"
OL,15,Fduring the confrontation.
OL,17,FThe jury heard Ms Elias describe the
OL,18,Fmanner of the pupil "as if looks could
OL,19,Fkill", before the pupil stabbed her in
OL,20,Fboth arms while shouting, "I want to
OL,21,Fkill you, I want to f*****g kill you".
