OL,3,CTeachers thought they were 'going to
OL,4,Cdie' during Ammanford school stabbing
OL,6,FThe 14-year-old defendant, who cannot
OL,7,Fbe identified for legal reasons, has
OL,8,Fpleaded guilty to three counts of
OL,9,Fwounding with intent and one of
OL,10,Fpossession of a bladed article on
OL,11,Fschool premises.
OL,13,FThe girl denies three counts of
OL,14,Fattempted murder in relation to the
OL,15,Fincident on April 24, when she was 13.
OL,17,FThe court also heard evidence from
OL,18,Fteacher Elizabeth Hopkin, who was
OL,19,Fstabbed in the neck during the attack.
