OL,3,CTeachers thought they were 'going to
OL,4,Cdie' during Ammanford school stabbing
OL,6,FMs Hopkin recalled how she grappled
OL,7,Fwith the pupil, spinning around each
OL,8,Fother, as she tried to retrieve the
OL,9,Fknife.
OL,11,FMs Hopkin said: "I saw the knife on
OL,12,Fthe floor, I tried to get it but I was
OL,13,Ftoo late. She (the pupil) came at me
OL,14,Fface-on and stabbed me in the neck, I
OL,15,Fthought this is it for me now, this is
OL,16,Fthe end, she's stabbed me in the neck."
