OL,3,CTeachers thought they were 'going to
OL,4,Cdie' during Ammanford school stabbing
OL,6,FGiving evidence in person, fellow
OL,7,Fassistant headteacher Steven Haggett
OL,8,Fdescribed how he had tried to calm the
OL,9,Fpupil who then stabbed another pupil
OL,10,Fin the shoulder.
OL,12,FMr Haggett told the jury: "I saw her
OL,13,Fmake contact with her shoulder with
OL,14,Fthe knife, she made a couple of
OL,15,Fattempts to stab her. She (the victim)
OL,16,Fstumbled and staggered and then fell
OL,17,Fdown onto the floor."
OL,19,FThe trial continues.
